-- Euro Weakens to Less Than $1.21 for First Time Since June 2010
-- B y   D a v i d   G o o d m a n
-- 2012-07-23T06:06:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-23/euro-weakens-to-less-than-1-21-for-first-time-since-june-2010.html
The euro fell against the dollar,
weakening below $1.21 for the first time in more than two years.  The 17-nation shared currency slid 0.5 percent to $1.2097
as of 7:04 a.m. London time after falling to as low as $1.2093,
the lowest since June 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Goodman in London at 
